# Full Model Review: Pros, Cons & Potential Problems

Here is a model-by-model review of your current [models.py](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py).

---

## 1. [Category](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#4-15)
```python
class Category(models.Model):
    title = models.CharField(max_length=200)
    slug = models.SlugField(max_length=200, unique=True)
```
| Pros | Cons / Problems |
| :--- | :--- |
| ✅ `slug` is unique — good for clean URLs | ⚠️ No `related_name` needed here, it's fine |
| ✅ Has timestamps | ✅ No issues found |

---

## 2. [Course](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#16-29)
```python
category = models.ForeignKey(Category, related_name='courses', on_delete=models.CASCADE)
instructor = models.ForeignKey(User, related_name='courses_created', on_delete=models.CASCADE)
```
| Pros | Cons / Problems |
| :--- | :--- |
| ✅ Good `related_name` choices | ⚠️ `on_delete=CASCADE` on instructor means if you delete the teacher, ALL their courses disappear. Consider `models.SET_NULL` with `null=True` |
| ✅ Has image field | ✅ Slug is unique |

---

## 3. [Module](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#30-67)
```python
completion_percentage  # @property
is_finished(self, user)  # method
```
| Pros | Cons / Problems |
| :--- | :--- |
| ✅ [is_finished](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#54-67) is per-user — great! | ❌ [completion_percentage](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#47-53) still uses `self.lessons.filter(is_done=True)` but you REMOVED `is_done` from Lesson! This will **crash**. You need to update it to use [UserLessonProgress](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#88-97) |
| ✅ [is_finished](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#54-67) checks both lessons and quizzes | ❌ Same problem: [is_finished](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#54-67) line 57 still checks `self.lessons.filter(is_done=True)`. Needs to use [UserLessonProgress](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#88-97) too |

