## 5. [UserLessonProgress](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#88-97) ⭐ (NEW)
```python
class UserLessonProgress(models.Model):
    user = models.ForeignKey(User, on_delete=models.CASCADE)
    lesson = models.ForeignKey(Lesson, on_delete=models.CASCADE)
    is_done = models.BooleanField(default=False)
```
| Pros | Cons / Problems |
| :--- | :--- |
| ✅ Per-user tracking — professional! | ❌ **Missing `unique_together`!** Right now, you can accidentally create 5 rows for the same user + same lesson. You need to add this to prevent duplicates: |

```python
class Meta:
    unique_together = ['user', 'lesson']
```
This ensures **one row per user per lesson**. Without it, your database could have duplicate entries.

---

## 6. [Quiz](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#102-124)
```python
number_of_try = models.IntegerField(default=0)  # OLD global counter
get_user_attempts_today(self, user)  # NEW per-user method
```
| Pros | Cons / Problems |
| :--- | :--- |
| ✅ [get_user_attempts_today](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#120-124) is per-user and daily — great! | ⚠️ `number_of_try` field is still in the model but no longer used. It's "dead code". You can remove it later and make a migration |

