## 7. [Question](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#126-136) & [Choice](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#137-144)
| Pros | Cons / Problems |
| :--- | :--- |
| ✅ Clean and simple | ⚠️ [Choice](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#137-144) has no protection against having zero correct answers or multiple correct answers per question. A quiz could break if an admin forgets to mark any choice as correct |

